[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":44},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Ftags\u002FCSS-Design-Patterns\u002F":3,"tag-page:en:CSS-Design-Patterns:1":4,"author-stats:en:full":41},null,{"tag":5,"slug":6,"posts":7,"total":39,"totalPages":40},"CSS Design Patterns","CSS-Design-Patterns",[8,17,24,31],{"url":9,"title":10,"date":11,"updated":11,"category":12,"tags":13,"description":15,"readingMinutes":16},"\u002Fen\u002Fcss\u002F2020\u002F05\u002F23\u002Fcss-design-patterns-sass-7-1-pattern\u002F","CSS Design Patterns — Sass 7-1 Pattern","2020-05-23 21:00:52","CSS",[5,14,12],"7-1 Pattern","The 7-1 pattern is about organising your directory structure. Back when you had to dump all your CSS in one place, maintenance was painful. Sass lets you use `@import` plus folder organisation — that's the 7-1 pattern.","2",{"url":18,"title":19,"date":20,"updated":20,"category":12,"tags":21,"description":23,"readingMinutes":16},"\u002Fen\u002Fcss\u002F2020\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fcss-design-patterns-bem\u002F","CSS Design Patterns — BEM","2020-05-17 15:33:48",[5,22,12],"BEM","BEM is a CSS design pattern that makes class architecture easier to maintain. The main downside is overly long class names — but plenty of real projects still use it.",{"url":25,"title":26,"date":27,"updated":27,"category":12,"tags":28,"description":30,"readingMinutes":16},"\u002Fen\u002Fcss\u002F2020\u002F05\u002F17\u002Fcss-design-patterns-oocss\u002F","CSS Design Patterns — OOCSS","2020-05-17 12:53:41",[5,29,12],"OOCSS","OOCSS is another CSS design pattern. The most prominent framework using it is Bootstrap.",{"url":32,"title":33,"date":34,"updated":34,"category":12,"tags":35,"description":37,"readingMinutes":38},"\u002Fen\u002Fcss\u002F2020\u002F05\u002F16\u002Fcss-design-patterns-smacss\u002F","CSS Design Patterns — SMACSS","2020-05-16 19:59:52",[5,36,12],"SMACSS","CSS design patterns are concepts, conventions, and ways of thinking that improve dev and maintenance efficiency. Let's start with SMACSS.","4",